                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.00/720: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 29, 3 p.m. The Department considers that forcible occupation of the
                    Princeton expedition field headquarters in the Sanjak by Turkish troops would be
                    a violation of Article 3 of the Convention between the United States and France
                    regarding Rights in Syria and the Lebanon. You should inform the High
                    Commissioner to this effect and request him to take such steps as may become
                    necessary to protect the vested American property rights involved unless in the
                    opinion of the expedition authorities such action on your part might be
                    prejudicial to their long range interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
